About Us:

Hum TV is a 24-hour Pakistani entertainment TV channel based in Karachi. It is the first brand of Hum Network Limited (KSE:HUMNL).[2] Hum Network Limited was known as Eye Television Network Limited prior to January 21, 2011.[3] Hum TV began its transmission on January 17, 2005.

Programs:

List of programs broadcast by Hum TV Serials Sanjha (2011–present) Humsafar (Rerun:2011-2012) Nadamat (2012-present) Mehar Bano aur Shah Bano (2012-present) Mata-e-Jaan Hai Tu (2012-present) Durr-e-Shahwar (2012-present) Ishq Junoon Deewangi (Rerun:2012) Bilqees Kaur (2012-present)

Soaps:

Uttaran (2010-present) Mujhay Roothnay Na Daina (2011–present) Mujhay Sandal Kar Do (2011–present) Ahmed Habib Ki Betiyan (2011-present)

Sitcoms:

Extras (The Mango People) (2011–present) One Way Ticket (2011-present) Fun Khana (2012-present) [edit]Series Kitni Girhain Baqi Hain (2011–present) Susral Ke Rung Anokhe (2012-present)

Other Shows:

Morning Shows Jago Pakistan Jago (2011–present)

Cooking Shows Chef At Home (2011–present)

General Junoon Kuch Kar Dikhane Ka Pakistani Planet Bollywood Disney Cinemagic

Availability: Hum TV is available in many countries mostly, via satellite, some via cable. The channel is available in parts of Middle East, Africa and all of Asia but not in Europe. The channel is currently broadcasting on PAS-10 (Panam Sat) on Frequency: 3774 H S/R: 3300 FEC: 3/4. In March 2010, Hum TV was officially launched in North America on Dish Network.

Hum TV USA:

Hum TV USA was launched and designed to cater to viewers in the United States. The channel’s theme incorporates both Pakistani and American-specific content and broadcasts identical shows aired on the mainstream Hum TV. All shows and programs are televised in accordance with flexible American standard timings. Hum TV is not available in the United Kingdom but its programs can be viewed on Youtube.
